Class RequestInfoPost

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.temple.howcanihelpapp.RequestInfoPost
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable
    public class RequestInfoPost
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    The purpose of this class is to provide a unit of information for map markers where users are able to recognize information regarding a user's donation or request posting

    • Field Detail

      • title

        java.lang.String title
        title indicates the main heading that captures the essence of what the user looks for dateTimePosted indicates the time and date that the post was published onto the app urgent indicates whether a request is high priority ableToRelocate indicates whether user is free to locate elsewhere, related to issues regarding mobility (e.g. disability) latlng indicates the coordinates where the marker is located postId is the ID number for the RequestInfoPost that is made
